 Right.

00:03:44.320 --> 00:03:47.200
 So that's kind of like my core

00:03:47.200 --> 00:03:49.890
 philosophy behind it, this idea

00:03:49.890 --> 00:03:52.680
 that the way that we develop

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:54.730
 beliefs about ourselves, that

00:03:54.730 --> 00:03:56.700
 we reinforce our self-image,

00:03:56.700 --> 00:03:58.600
 that we develop our identity

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:00.660
 to a certain degree, is largely

00:04:00.660 --> 00:04:02.680
 reinforced by the experiences

00:04:02.680 --> 00:04:04.600
 and behaviors that we perform

00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:05.600
 over time.

00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:06.690
 So some aspects of your

00:04:06.690 --> 00:04:08.290
 identity are relatively fixed,

00:04:08.290 --> 00:04:09.780
 like, for example, if you're

00:04:09.780 --> 00:04:10.680
 tall or

00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:11.680
 short.

00:04:11.680 --> 00:04:13.520
 Even that idea that I am tall

00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:14.960
 or I am short, that's

00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:16.040
 reinforced.

00:04:16.040 --> 00:04:17.650
 You learn that through

00:04:17.650 --> 00:04:19.400
 experiences in life.

00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:21.140
 Now there are many aspects of

00:04:21.140 --> 00:04:22.810
 your identity that are less

00:04:22.810 --> 00:04:24.760
 fixed than that, but are still

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:27.000
 reinforced by your experiences.

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:29.550
 So if you write one sentence

00:04:29.550 --> 00:04:32.660
 today, you probably don't think

00:04:32.660 --> 00:04:35.450
 about yourself as I am a writer

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:35.880
.

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:37.350
 But if you do that every day

00:04:37.350 --> 00:04:38.950
 for six months or nine months

00:04:38.950 --> 00:04:40.600
 or a year, at some point you

00:04:40.600 --> 00:04:41.950
 turn around and you think, "Huh

00:04:41.950 --> 00:04:43.200
, maybe I am the kind of person

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:44.040
 who is a writer."

00:04:44.040 --> 00:04:46.280
 Or if you study biology every

00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:49.080
 Tuesday night for 20 minutes,

00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:51.320
 you at some point think, "I

00:04:51.320 --> 00:04:52.320
 guess I'm studious.

00:04:52.320 --> 00:04:54.000
 I keep doing this every week.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:55.040
 Maybe this is the kind of

00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:55.760
 person I am."

00:04:55.760 --> 00:04:57.570
 And so I like that idea that

00:04:57.570 --> 00:04:59.560
 our habits are like votes for

00:04:59.560 --> 00:05:01.640
 the type of person we believe

00:05:01.640 --> 00:05:03.630
 that we are, that they build up

00:05:03.630 --> 00:05:05.090
 evidence of looking at

00:05:05.090 --> 00:05:07.080
 ourselves in a certain way.

00:05:07.080 --> 00:05:08.840
 And I like to phrase it that

00:05:08.840 --> 00:05:10.840
 way not only because I believe

00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:12.560
 that it's true, but also

00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:14.440
 beliefs and behavior are kind

00:05:14.440 --> 00:05:15.920
 of a two-way street.

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:17.650
 So you'll hear people say

00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:19.870
 things like, "Just be positive

00:05:19.870 --> 00:05:22.040
 or just believe in yourself or

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:23.720
 fake it till you make it," or

00:05:23.720 --> 00:05:24.920
 things like that.

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:27.060
 And there's nothing necessarily

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:28.660
 wrong with fake it till you

00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:29.400
 make it.

00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:30.790
 It's fine to be positive and

00:05:30.790 --> 00:05:32.500
 believe things about yourself,

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:33.920
 but it's a very short-term

00:05:33.920 --> 00:05:35.840
 strategy because fake it till

00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:37.290
 you make it is asking you to

00:05:37.290 --> 00:05:38.880
 believe something about

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:39.520
 yourself

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:41.480
 without having evidence for it.

00:05:41.480 --> 00:05:42.860
 It's like that kind of

00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:43.920
 visualization stuff or mantra

00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:44.970
 stuff where you look at

00:05:44.970 --> 00:05:45.480
 yourself

00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:46.250
 in the mirror and you tell

00:05:46.250 --> 00:05:47.200
 yourself, "I am a writer.

00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:49.120
 I am a writer," even though you

00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:50.700
 haven't written yet.

00:05:50.700 --> 00:05:52.040
 And so what I'm saying is

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:53.290
 similar, but I think

00:05:53.290 --> 00:05:55.020
 importantly different in the

00:05:55.020 --> 00:05:56.360
 sense that you

00:05:56.360 --> 00:05:58.040
 let the behavior lead the way

00:05:58.040 --> 00:05:59.640
 rather than the belief.

00:05:59.640 --> 00:06:01.110
 And I think that's the best

00:06:01.110 --> 00:06:02.850
 lever we have for changing the

00:06:02.850 --> 00:06:04.680
 way that we look at ourselves,

00:06:04.680 --> 00:06:06.060
 which is to say, show up and

00:06:06.060 --> 00:06:07.670
 write a sentence every day, and

00:06:07.670 --> 00:06:09.000
 soon you're going to have

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:09.320
 something

00:06:09.320 --> 00:06:11.440
 to root that new identity of, "

00:06:11.440 --> 00:06:12.800
I am a writer in."

00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:14.140
 And it's a much more, I think,

00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:15.340
 robust and long-term way of

00:06:15.340 --> 00:06:16.480
 changing how you look at

00:06:16.480 --> 00:06:17.480
 yourself.

