 There's a big difference

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:03.010
 between going in where you feel

00:15:03.010 --> 00:15:04.400
 like, "Oh, maybe I'm a few

00:15:04.400 --> 00:15:05.400
 pounds overweight."

00:15:05.400 --> 00:15:07.290
 Going in and being 200 pounds

00:15:07.290 --> 00:15:08.160
 overweight.

00:15:08.160 --> 00:15:10.410
 There's a big difference

00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:12.730
 between going in even as a

00:15:12.730 --> 00:15:15.760
 white male compared to, there's

00:15:15.760 --> 00:15:17.100
 a big difference going in and

00:15:17.100 --> 00:15:18.630
 feeling like, "Well, I've done

00:15:18.630 --> 00:15:20.040
 these exercises before so

00:15:20.040 --> 00:15:21.850
 I'm not completely out of my

00:15:21.850 --> 00:15:22.880
 element."

00:15:22.880 --> 00:15:26.770
 And I'm wondering how, I mean,

00:15:26.770 --> 00:15:30.160
 are habits like that achievable

00:15:30.160 --> 00:15:32.520
 because of privilege

00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:34.160
 and context and other things.

00:15:34.160 --> 00:15:36.340
 How much does that play into it

00:15:36.340 --> 00:15:36.640
?

00:15:36.640 --> 00:15:38.990
 And if someone is walking in

00:15:38.990 --> 00:15:41.570
 and they're 200 pounds

00:15:41.570 --> 00:15:44.440
 overweight, do they still have

00:15:44.440 --> 00:15:44.520
 the

00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:46.700
 same chance of progress and

00:15:46.700 --> 00:15:47.680
 success?

00:15:47.680 --> 00:15:49.520
 It just feels like such a big

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:51.560
 mountain for them to go over.

00:15:51.560 --> 00:15:52.720
 For sure.

00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:53.720
 Yeah.

00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:55.330
 So, this is one reason why I

00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:56.870
 think starting with small

00:15:56.870 --> 00:15:58.270
 habits is so incredibly

00:15:58.270 --> 00:15:58.960
 important

00:15:58.960 --> 00:16:00.410
 because a lot of the time when

00:16:00.410 --> 00:16:02.000
 we think about the outcome that

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:03.640
 you want, so just to continue

00:16:03.640 --> 00:16:05.080
 your weight loss or exercise

00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:06.820
 example, everybody gets wrapped

00:16:06.820 --> 00:16:08.240
 up and like, "Oh, I want to

00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:08.440
 lose

00:16:08.440 --> 00:16:10.590
 100 pounds or I want to lose 20

00:16:10.590 --> 00:16:12.160
 pounds or whatever the number

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:12.640
 is."

00:16:12.640 --> 00:16:14.160
 But you forget about there,

00:16:14.160 --> 00:16:15.490
 like all these little log

00:16:15.490 --> 00:16:17.130
istical and emotional details

00:16:17.130 --> 00:16:17.440
 that

00:16:17.440 --> 00:16:19.620
 come along with starting a new

00:16:19.620 --> 00:16:20.360
 habit.

00:16:20.360 --> 00:16:21.620
 So I'll often tell the story

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:23.100
 about, I have this reader who,

00:16:23.100 --> 00:16:24.720
 he ended up losing over 100

00:16:24.720 --> 00:16:25.720
 pounds.

00:16:25.720 --> 00:16:26.850
 And one of the first things he

00:16:26.850 --> 00:16:28.010
 did was he went to the gym, but

00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:29.000
 he wasn't allowed to

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:30.260
 stay for longer than five

00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:30.880
 minutes.

00:16:30.880 --> 00:16:32.610
 So he drove to the gym, got out

00:16:32.610 --> 00:16:33.780
 of the car, did half an

00:16:33.780 --> 00:16:35.720
 exercise, got back in the car,

00:16:35.720 --> 00:16:36.880
 drove home.

00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:38.190
 And it sounds ridiculous to

00:16:38.190 --> 00:16:38.760
 people.

00:16:38.760 --> 00:16:40.020
 It sounds silly because it's

00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:41.600
 like, "Well, clearly exercising

00:16:41.600 --> 00:16:42.720
 for five minutes is not

00:16:42.720 --> 00:16:43.720
 going to get you in shape."

00:16:43.720 --> 00:16:44.720
 I guess not.

00:16:44.720 --> 00:16:46.560
 But what you realize is he was

00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:48.620
 mastering the art of showing up

00:16:48.620 --> 00:16:48.840
.

00:16:48.840 --> 00:16:50.380
 He was becoming the type of

00:16:50.380 --> 00:16:51.990
 person that drove to the gym

00:16:51.990 --> 00:16:52.800
 every day.

00:16:52.800 --> 00:16:54.500
 And when you're in that state,

00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:56.130
 for him at that point, that was

00:16:56.130 --> 00:16:57.520
 the biggest shift was,

00:16:57.520 --> 00:16:59.150
 "Can I just become the type of

00:16:59.150 --> 00:17:00.770
 person who gets in here, who

00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:02.480
 overcomes the uncertainty

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:04.290
 or feeling uncomfortable or

00:17:04.290 --> 00:17:05.600
 feeling judged?"

00:17:05.600 --> 00:17:07.620
 And all those things are very

00:17:07.620 --> 00:17:09.490
 real hurdles to building a

00:17:09.490 --> 00:17:10.240
 habit.

00:17:10.240 --> 00:17:11.090
 There are all these little

00:17:11.090 --> 00:17:11.920
 questions that need to be

00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:12.860
 answered for something like

00:17:12.860 --> 00:17:13.360
 that.

00:17:13.360 --> 00:17:14.940
 Like, "Okay, I want to go to

00:17:14.940 --> 00:17:15.640
 the gym.

00:17:15.640 --> 00:17:16.960
 Well, what time am I going to

00:17:16.960 --> 00:17:17.280
 go?

00:17:17.280 --> 00:17:18.770
 Am I going to go before work or

00:17:18.770 --> 00:17:19.600
 after work?

00:17:19.600 --> 00:17:21.120
 What gym will I go to?

00:17:21.120 --> 00:17:22.420
 What route am I going to take

00:17:22.420 --> 00:17:23.160
 to get there?

00:17:23.160 --> 00:17:24.560
 Do I need to bring a water

00:17:24.560 --> 00:17:26.310
 bottle or is there like a water

00:17:26.310 --> 00:17:27.760
 fountain at the gym?"

00:17:27.760 --> 00:17:29.590
 And all those little questions

00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:31.410
 like that, like whether or not

00:17:31.410 --> 00:17:32.960
 there's a water fountain

00:17:32.960 --> 00:17:34.840
 at the gym, it sounds small.

00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:35.860
 But if you already feel

00:17:35.860 --> 00:17:37.310
 uncomfortable and feel like you

00:17:37.310 --> 00:17:38.520
 don't belong and then you

00:17:38.520 --> 00:17:38.800
 always

00:17:38.800 --> 00:17:39.560
 forget to bring your water

00:17:39.560 --> 00:17:40.450
 bottle and you're like, "Oh,

00:17:40.450 --> 00:17:41.430
 there's nothing ever, and there

00:17:41.430 --> 00:17:41.560
's

00:17:41.560 --> 00:17:42.880
 never anything to drink there."

00:17:42.880 --> 00:17:44.290
 That's enough friction to get

00:17:44.290 --> 00:17:45.760
 you to quit in the beginning.

00:17:45.760 --> 00:17:47.020
 So starting with something

00:17:47.020 --> 00:17:48.550
 simple, like, "All I'm going to

00:17:48.550 --> 00:17:50.120
 do is I'm going to show up and

00:17:50.120 --> 00:17:51.790
 I'm going to do one exercise

00:17:51.790 --> 00:17:53.540
 for five minutes and then I'm

00:17:53.540 --> 00:17:54.600
 going to go."

00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:55.950
 That I think is a good way to

00:17:55.950 --> 00:17:56.480
 start.

00:17:56.480 --> 00:17:57.880
 And it reminds me of what

00:17:57.880 --> 00:17:59.600
 Steven Pressfield wrote.

00:17:59.600 --> 00:18:00.570
 I think it was in the War of

00:18:00.570 --> 00:18:01.760
 Art where he said something to

00:18:01.760 --> 00:18:02.840
 the effect of like, "If

00:18:02.840 --> 00:18:04.310
 you sit down each day at the

00:18:04.310 --> 00:18:05.650
 computer and you do your

00:18:05.650 --> 00:18:07.260
 writing, at some point, at

00:18:07.260 --> 00:18:07.720
 first

00:18:07.720 --> 00:18:09.240
 it feels uncomfortable, but at

00:18:09.240 --> 00:18:10.610
 some point that becomes your

00:18:10.610 --> 00:18:11.400
 territory."

00:18:11.400 --> 00:18:13.730
 And I really like that phrasing

00:18:13.730 --> 00:18:15.890
 of it because for an animal,

00:18:15.890 --> 00:18:17.920
 for a wolf or something, a

00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:19.610
 piece of land does not become

00:18:19.610 --> 00:18:21.310
 their territory unless they

00:18:21.310 --> 00:18:23.000
 spend time in it, right?

00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:24.920
 Unless they are there each day.

00:18:24.920 --> 00:18:26.340
 It has to become comfortable

00:18:26.340 --> 00:18:26.840
 first.

00:18:26.840 --> 00:18:28.420
 And so for many people building

00:18:28.420 --> 00:18:30.130
 habits, whether that's getting

00:18:30.130 --> 00:18:31.440
 into the gym or going to the

00:18:31.440 --> 00:18:32.940
 yoga studio or sitting your

00:18:32.940 --> 00:18:34.630
 butt in the chair and writing,

00:18:34.630 --> 00:18:36.060
 you need to make that space

00:18:36.060 --> 00:18:36.400
 your

00:18:36.400 --> 00:18:37.400
 territory.

00:18:37.400 --> 00:18:39.350
 And the very first step is not

00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:40.800
 getting a result.

00:18:40.800 --> 00:18:42.440
 It's spending time there.

00:18:42.440 --> 00:18:44.120
 It's making that little bit of

00:18:44.120 --> 00:18:45.800
 land a zone where you feel like

00:18:45.800 --> 00:18:47.360
, "This is where I belong

00:18:47.360 --> 00:18:48.360
 each day."

00:18:48.360 --> 00:18:50.180
 And that's a big emotional

00:18:50.180 --> 00:18:52.340
 hurdle to cross before you even

00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:54.600
 worry about any of the physical

00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:56.480
 or actual technical things to

00:18:56.480 --> 00:18:56.880
 do.

00:18:56.880 --> 00:18:57.880
 Yeah.

00:18:57.880 --> 00:19:00.070
 And I mean, the other thing

00:19:00.070 --> 00:19:02.480
 that helped is I went with my

00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:04.360
 wife and it's funny because

00:19:04.360 --> 00:19:06.650
 I felt like I'm like Mr. Conf

00:19:06.650 --> 00:19:09.140
ident, but she was like, at one

00:19:09.140 --> 00:19:11.600
 point, she's like, "Justin,

00:19:11.600 --> 00:19:13.840
 you are so nervous right now."

00:19:13.840 --> 00:19:16.000
 She could tell how nervous I

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:16.600
 was.

00:19:16.600 --> 00:19:18.560
 But I thought I was keeping it

00:19:18.560 --> 00:19:19.760
 all together.

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:21.850
 And it just reminded me of, I'd

00:19:21.850 --> 00:19:23.700
 been to gyms from the time I

00:19:23.700 --> 00:19:25.240
 was in grade nine all the

00:19:25.240 --> 00:19:26.680
 way through college.

00:19:26.680 --> 00:19:28.070
 It wasn't like it was

00:19:28.070 --> 00:19:30.690
 unfamiliar, but I was nervous

00:19:30.690 --> 00:19:32.400
 because it was unfamiliar.

00:19:32.400 --> 00:19:34.480
 There had been a seven-year gap

00:19:34.480 --> 00:19:36.320
 and now I was exploring this

00:19:36.320 --> 00:19:38.240
 again, worried about what

00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:39.900
 these people are thinking about

00:19:39.900 --> 00:19:40.240
 me.

00:19:40.240 --> 00:19:42.200
 "Wow, that guy looks like he's

00:19:42.200 --> 00:19:43.800
 way more fit than me."

00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:45.430
 All these thoughts go through

00:19:45.430 --> 00:19:46.360
 your head.

00:19:46.360 --> 00:19:49.110
 And so, yeah, I think kind of

00:19:49.110 --> 00:19:51.870
 figuring out how you can make a

00:19:51.870 --> 00:19:54.240
 step and sometimes maybe

00:19:54.240 --> 00:19:56.110
 it's like going with somebody

00:19:56.110 --> 00:19:57.910
 so you at least have some

00:19:57.910 --> 00:19:59.270
 emotional, because it's

00:19:59.270 --> 00:20:00.240
 emotional.

00:20:00.240 --> 00:20:01.860
 It's nice to have someone to

00:20:01.860 --> 00:20:03.490
 kind of share the emotional

00:20:03.490 --> 00:20:04.720
 burden, right?

00:20:04.720 --> 00:20:05.720
 For sure.

00:20:05.720 --> 00:20:07.520
 Well, if you come, the thing

00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:09.270
 that ultimately what you're

00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:11.160
 looking to do is, like we just

00:20:11.160 --> 00:20:12.460
 said, feel like it's part of

00:20:12.460 --> 00:20:13.360
 your territory.

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:14.570
 And because there are other

00:20:14.570 --> 00:20:15.980
 people in that space, what that

00:20:15.980 --> 00:20:17.320
 also means is you're looking

00:20:17.320 --> 00:20:18.930
 to feel like you're part of the

00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:20.720
 tribe who goes there, right?

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:22.350
 You belong with the other

00:20:22.350 --> 00:20:24.360
 people who are in that room.

00:20:24.360 --> 00:20:26.700
 And so it helps to, what is a

00:20:26.700 --> 00:20:27.600
 tribe?

00:20:27.600 --> 00:20:28.720
 Well, it's a group of people

00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:29.900
 that you get along with, that

00:20:29.900 --> 00:20:31.440
 you bond with, that you belong

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:33.450
 to over something else, over

00:20:33.450 --> 00:20:35.200
 some shared interest.

00:20:35.200 --> 00:20:36.420
 And in other words, it's a

00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:37.480
 group in a lot of ways of

00:20:37.480 --> 00:20:39.200
 friends, friends who share some

00:20:39.200 --> 00:20:40.200
 kind of interest.

00:20:40.200 --> 00:20:41.840
 So these are your gym friends.

00:20:41.840 --> 00:20:43.600
 Well, if you go with your wife,

00:20:43.600 --> 00:20:45.320
 then you automatically have at

00:20:45.320 --> 00:20:47.060
 least one person in the tribe

00:20:47.060 --> 00:20:47.360
 that

00:20:47.360 --> 00:20:49.320
 you are friends with, that you

00:20:49.320 --> 00:20:50.520
 do belong with.

00:20:50.520 --> 00:20:52.130
 And so I think that helps you

00:20:52.130 --> 00:20:54.020
 get over that hurdle a little

00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:54.320
 bit.

00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:55.940
 You're no longer facing that

00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:57.160
 challenge alone.

00:20:57.160 --> 00:20:58.980
 Before it was like, I am trying

00:20:58.980 --> 00:20:59.760
 to get fit.

00:20:59.760 --> 00:21:01.930
 Now it is we are trying to get

00:21:01.930 --> 00:21:02.480
 fit.

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:04.320
 And that helps a lot with the

00:21:04.320 --> 00:21:06.240
 kind of the mental feeling of

00:21:06.240 --> 00:21:08.160
 like, do I belong or not?

00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:09.160
 Yeah.

00:21:09.160 --> 00:21:11.600
 So I don't mean to stay on this

00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:13.950
 too long, but it's so fresh

00:21:13.950 --> 00:21:16.240
 that the other thing I found

00:21:16.240 --> 00:21:18.030
 myself doing, because I'm

00:21:18.030 --> 00:21:19.910
 interested in the emotional

00:21:19.910 --> 00:21:21.800
 friction behind habits.

00:21:21.800 --> 00:21:23.840
 And so the other thing I was

00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:26.120
 doing is I was going in there

00:21:26.120 --> 00:21:28.120
 and I'm uncomfortable.

00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:29.880
 So I'm trying to act really

00:21:29.880 --> 00:21:32.520
 tough, but I'm not tough at all

00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:32.880
.

00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:34.560
 But when people look at me, I'm

00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:36.310
 kind of like scowling when like

00:21:36.310 --> 00:21:37.800
 I'm not being friendly.

00:21:37.800 --> 00:21:40.160
 I'm not being myself.

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:42.990
 And I was thinking about that

00:21:42.990 --> 00:21:45.730
 and thinking like when you're

00:21:45.730 --> 00:21:48.240
 kind of inward focused and

00:21:48.240 --> 00:21:49.200
 you're in a new environment and

00:21:49.200 --> 00:21:50.130
 you're trying to develop a new

00:21:50.130 --> 00:21:51.080
 habit, but you're inward

00:21:51.080 --> 00:21:52.240
 focused,

00:21:52.240 --> 00:21:55.210
 it really is, it doesn't really

00:21:55.210 --> 00:21:56.000
 help.

00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:56.840
 And so I had to kind of turn

00:21:56.840 --> 00:21:57.920
 that around and go, okay, I got

00:21:57.920 --> 00:21:58.880
 to start being friendly.

00:21:58.880 --> 00:22:00.370
 I got to start saying hi to

00:22:00.370 --> 00:22:02.310
 these people, because if I wave

00:22:02.310 --> 00:22:04.000
 at this person and it feels

00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:06.820
 good, like they respond with a

00:22:06.820 --> 00:22:07.840
 smile.

00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:08.940
 And that happens again next

00:22:08.940 --> 00:22:09.320
 time.

00:22:09.320 --> 00:22:11.620
 And again, next time, that's a

00:22:11.620 --> 00:22:13.920
 little bit of a reward for me.

00:22:13.920 --> 00:22:15.050
 That's going to keep me going

00:22:15.050 --> 00:22:15.560
 to the gym.

00:22:15.560 --> 00:22:17.850
 But if I keep going here with

00:22:17.850 --> 00:22:19.530
 this like tough scowl on my

00:22:19.530 --> 00:22:21.760
 face, and it's hard because you

00:22:21.760 --> 00:22:25.840
 feel like you don't belong.

00:22:25.840 --> 00:22:27.280
 You feel nervous.

00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:29.320
 And you kind of default to

00:22:29.320 --> 00:22:31.560
 these weird behaviors.

00:22:31.560 --> 00:22:33.710
 And it took a little bit of

00:22:33.710 --> 00:22:36.670
 time, but I realized, okay, now

00:22:36.670 --> 00:22:39.040
 I got to get in the habit of

00:22:39.040 --> 00:22:39.640
 smiling

00:22:39.640 --> 00:22:41.180
 and saying hello when I'm in

00:22:41.180 --> 00:22:42.920
 the gym, not just being like in

00:22:42.920 --> 00:22:44.520
 my own zone and pretending

00:22:44.520 --> 00:22:46.760
 I'm somebody I'm not, right?

00:22:46.760 --> 00:22:48.090
 Well, that's one thing that

00:22:48.090 --> 00:22:49.260
 kind of helps you start to

00:22:49.260 --> 00:22:50.640
 belong or become part of the

00:22:50.640 --> 00:22:52.280
 rest of the tribe.

00:22:52.280 --> 00:22:53.510
 Just a friendly behavior helps

00:22:53.510 --> 00:22:54.310
 you start to develop

00:22:54.310 --> 00:22:55.550
 friendships with some of those

00:22:55.550 --> 00:22:55.860
 other

00:22:55.860 --> 00:22:56.860
 people that are there.

00:22:56.860 --> 00:22:57.860
 Yeah.

00:22:57.860 --> 00:22:59.300
 A study that I wanted to cite

00:22:59.300 --> 00:23:01.040
 in Atomic Habits, but I couldn

00:23:01.040 --> 00:23:02.560
't find it to track it down.

00:23:02.560 --> 00:23:05.090
 But I read about it years ago,

00:23:05.090 --> 00:23:07.720
 where the YMCA ran a survey.

00:23:07.720 --> 00:23:09.490
 And when they surveyed people

00:23:09.490 --> 00:23:11.250
 who were joining the gym, the

00:23:11.250 --> 00:23:12.800
 thing that got them to join

00:23:12.800 --> 00:23:13.200
 were

00:23:13.200 --> 00:23:14.790
 the different classes offered,

00:23:14.790 --> 00:23:16.140
 the equipment that was in the

00:23:16.140 --> 00:23:17.560
 gym, basically facilities

00:23:17.560 --> 00:23:19.110
 and features were the things

00:23:19.110 --> 00:23:20.460
 that got people in for the

00:23:20.460 --> 00:23:21.320
 first time.

00:23:21.320 --> 00:23:22.410
 But then when they surveyed

00:23:22.410 --> 00:23:23.590
 members who had been there for

00:23:23.590 --> 00:23:24.840
 over a year, the thing that

00:23:24.840 --> 00:23:26.390
 got people to stick, nobody

00:23:26.390 --> 00:23:27.620
 mentioned features or

00:23:27.620 --> 00:23:28.500
 facilities.

00:23:28.500 --> 00:23:30.300
 Everybody mentioned friendships

00:23:30.300 --> 00:23:30.500
.

00:23:30.500 --> 00:23:31.840
 And so the people who actually

00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:33.200
 stayed at the gym or kept their

00:23:33.200 --> 00:23:34.420
 membership were the ones

00:23:34.420 --> 00:23:35.650
 who ended up developing

00:23:35.650 --> 00:23:37.250
 friendships with other people

00:23:37.250 --> 00:23:37.780
 there.

00:23:37.780 --> 00:23:38.780
 And I think you're right.

00:23:38.780 --> 00:23:40.140
 Ultimately, the thing that gets

00:23:40.140 --> 00:23:41.220
 you to come back is like, do I

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:42.180
 enjoy coming here?

00:23:42.180 --> 00:23:43.450
 Does it mean I get to see some

00:23:43.450 --> 00:23:44.300
 of my friends?

00:23:44.300 --> 00:23:45.450
 Does it mean I get to hang out

00:23:45.450 --> 00:23:46.380
 with people I like?

00:23:46.380 --> 00:23:48.460
 Or, you know, it's really the

00:23:48.460 --> 00:23:50.750
 sense of belonging that gets

00:23:50.750 --> 00:23:51.740
 habits to stick.

00:23:51.740 --> 00:23:53.290
 And the action itself is just

00:23:53.290 --> 00:23:54.920
 kind of like something that's

00:23:54.920 --> 00:23:56.480
 happening along the way.

00:23:56.480 --> 00:23:57.480
 Yes.

00:23:57.480 --> 00:23:58.730
 But there's a step before that

00:23:58.730 --> 00:23:59.980
 that we kind of skipped over,

00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:01.120
 which is like, how do you

00:24:01.120 --> 00:24:03.010
 even choose a habit in the

00:24:03.010 --> 00:24:04.200
 first place?

00:24:04.200 --> 00:24:06.200
 Like how does that happen?

00:24:06.200 --> 00:24:09.160
 In the sense of, I might not

00:24:09.160 --> 00:24:11.920
 know what's good for me.

00:24:11.920 --> 00:24:15.520
 So how does that come into this

00:24:15.520 --> 00:24:15.520
?

00:24:15.520 --> 00:24:16.520
 Yeah.

00:24:16.520 --> 00:24:17.420
 Well, there are a lot of ways

00:24:17.420 --> 00:24:18.360
 to answer that question.

00:24:18.360 --> 00:24:19.590
 So I'll just share a couple of

00:24:19.590 --> 00:24:20.920
 thoughts that come to mind.

00:24:20.920 --> 00:24:22.490
 So the first thought that comes

00:24:22.490 --> 00:24:24.070
 to mind is this question from,

00:24:24.070 --> 00:24:25.300
 I first heard from Seth

00:24:25.300 --> 00:24:26.920
 Godin, which I think is just a

00:24:26.920 --> 00:24:28.750
 great question, which is, what

00:24:28.750 --> 00:24:29.460
 is it for?

00:24:29.460 --> 00:24:30.520
 And so this is a question that

00:24:30.520 --> 00:24:31.610
 we need to ask ourselves when

00:24:31.610 --> 00:24:32.540
 we're trying to build a

00:24:32.540 --> 00:24:34.080
 new habit, which is, what is

00:24:34.080 --> 00:24:35.100
 this habit for?

00:24:35.100 --> 00:24:36.770
 What am I actually trying to

00:24:36.770 --> 00:24:37.860
 achieve here?

00:24:37.860 --> 00:24:39.490
 Because the correct habit to

00:24:39.490 --> 00:24:41.250
 choose is very different based

00:24:41.250 --> 00:24:42.940
 on what your goals are, what

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:44.710
 you're hoping to get as an

00:24:44.710 --> 00:24:47.090
 outcome, what kind of lifestyle

00:24:47.090 --> 00:24:48.020
 you want.

00:24:48.020 --> 00:24:49.830
 And so for example, the habit

00:24:49.830 --> 00:24:52.160
 of making 20 sales calls a day.

00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:53.680
 Well, if what it's for is to

00:24:53.680 --> 00:24:55.430
 increase revenue and to build a

00:24:55.430 --> 00:24:57.280
 successful business, that's

00:24:57.280 --> 00:24:58.880
 a wonderful thing.

00:24:58.880 --> 00:25:00.490
 If you hate making sales calls

00:25:00.490 --> 00:25:02.100
 and you want to spend less time

00:25:02.100 --> 00:25:03.440
 working and more time with

00:25:03.440 --> 00:25:04.700
 your family, that could be a

00:25:04.700 --> 00:25:06.000
 terrible habit to build.

00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:08.410
 It just depends on what it's

00:25:08.410 --> 00:25:09.080
 for.

00:25:09.080 --> 00:25:11.430
 So that's one question to ask,

00:25:11.430 --> 00:25:13.400
 but you are correct that we

00:25:13.400 --> 00:25:15.800
 often don't know what we need

00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:17.440
 in the moment.

00:25:17.440 --> 00:25:18.420
 And I think part of that is

00:25:18.420 --> 00:25:19.600
 just a challenge of life and a

00:25:19.600 --> 00:25:20.900
 challenge of self-awareness

00:25:20.900 --> 00:25:23.650
 and knowing what you need, but

00:25:23.650 --> 00:25:26.460
 life is a very complex system.

00:25:26.460 --> 00:25:28.030
 And so figuring out the right

00:25:28.030 --> 00:25:29.350
 thing for that is sometimes

00:25:29.350 --> 00:25:30.780
 just impossible or too many

00:25:30.780 --> 00:25:31.260
 moving

00:25:31.260 --> 00:25:32.260
 parts.

00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:34.820
 So I tend to default to two

00:25:34.820 --> 00:25:37.100
 possible answers.

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:38.480
 The first answer is, we all

00:25:38.480 --> 00:25:39.980
 need things that are so boring

00:25:39.980 --> 00:25:41.900
 that we don't think about them,

00:25:41.900 --> 00:25:43.150
 but are incredibly important

00:25:43.150 --> 00:25:44.260
 for showing up each day.

00:25:44.260 --> 00:25:46.860
 So did you sleep eight hours?

00:25:46.860 --> 00:25:48.320
 Are you drinking enough water?

00:25:48.320 --> 00:25:49.700
 Are you spending a little bit

00:25:49.700 --> 00:25:50.970
 of time walking outside or

00:25:50.970 --> 00:25:52.350
 getting a little bit of

00:25:52.350 --> 00:25:52.840
 sunlight?

00:25:52.840 --> 00:25:54.640
 Do you exercise consistently?

00:25:54.640 --> 00:25:56.580
 Whatever form is interesting to

00:25:56.580 --> 00:25:57.040
 you?

00:25:57.040 --> 00:25:58.210
 Are you spending some time

00:25:58.210 --> 00:25:59.390
 reading and soaking up new

00:25:59.390 --> 00:25:59.880
 ideas?

00:25:59.880 --> 00:26:01.330
 I'm not saying you have to do

00:26:01.330 --> 00:26:02.890
 all that stuff every day, but

00:26:02.890 --> 00:26:04.480
 my point is those are things

00:26:04.480 --> 00:26:05.920
 that most people would be like,

00:26:05.920 --> 00:26:07.260
 "Yeah, of course, you should

00:26:07.260 --> 00:26:08.480
 sleep and read more books

00:26:08.480 --> 00:26:09.480
 and exercise.

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:10.680
 Everybody knows that's good."

00:26:10.680 --> 00:26:12.400
 But your time is almost never

00:26:12.400 --> 00:26:14.100
 going to be wasted by making

00:26:14.100 --> 00:26:15.790
 sure you do one of those things

00:26:15.790 --> 00:26:16.840
.

00:26:16.840 --> 00:26:18.310
